The article discusses a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and Under Secretary of State for Public Diplomacy Judith McHale. McHale discusses the efforts made to highlight President Obama's speech in Ghana throughout Africa. The State Department used new media initiatives to engage with people and received thousands of questions and comments. They also worked with local media in African countries to broadcast the speech and organized events to view and discuss the speech. The article also touches on other topics such as healthcare reform and the controversy surrounding a CIA program.